place.name: EISEY
place.gazetteerText: EISEY, a parish in Cricklade district, Wilts; on the river Thames and on the Severn and Thames canal, contiguous with Gloucestershire, 1 mile NNE of Cricklade and 4¾ NE by E of Minety r. station. Acres, 1,840. Real property, with Latton, £7, 248. Pop., 193. Houses, 36. It includes the tything of Water-Eaton; and its post town is Cricklade. The living is a vicarage, annexed to the vicarage of Latton, in the diocese of Gloucester and Bristol. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
